---
title: Spiced Freekah Pilaf with Roasted Vegetables and Tomato Salsa
description: A great source of dietary fibre, iron and zinc, freekeh is a green grain made from young durum wheat which is roasted or smoked then polished to remove the shells.  With its distinct nutty, smoky flavour, freekeh can be cooked like rice, making it a go-to ingredient for things like this healthy spiced pilaf.  The tomato and herb salsa keeps the flavour fresh, whilst the addition of chickpeas, chopped pistachios and roasted veg make this a deliciously hearty and filling dish.
